        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Third-Party Surface in an Agentic Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A production agentic system is rarely built on first-party code alone. It pulls in LLM SDKs, vector-database clients, orchestration frameworks, REST API wrappers, and observability packages \u2014 each maintained by teams outside your organisation. Any one of those dependencies is a potential entry point: if an upstream package is compromised, the malicious code runs inside your agent with whatever permissions the agent holds."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Third-party risk in agentic systems is more severe than in ordinary web apps because the agent acts autonomously \u2014 a compromised dependency can exfiltrate data, send emails, or call external APIs without a human noticing immediately."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Risk Taxonomy"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Third-party risk vectors in agentic pipelines",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Six primary vectors flow into (or out of) a typical agentic pipeline. Arrows to the left represent inbound risk (code or data entering the pipeline); arrows to the right represent outbound risk (your credentials or data leaving through a third-party integration)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Python / Node Package Dependencies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dependency confusion, typosquatting, and direct compromise of legitimate packages are the highest-volume supply-chain attack classes. The fix is hash pinning combined with a private mirror."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "toml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pyproject.toml \u2014 lock every direct dependency to a specific hash\n[tool.pip-tools]\ngenerate_hashes = true\n\n# requirements.txt generated by pip-compile --generate-hashes\nanthropic==0.28.0 \\\n    --hash=sha256:c1a4b7e5...d902 \\\n    --hash=sha256:3b91e2a8...ff01\n\nlangchain-core==0.2.5 \\\n    --hash=sha256:a7f3d821...8c44\n\n# Pin private-mirror index so PyPI cannot inject lookalike packages\n--index-url https://pypi.internal.example.com/simple/\n--extra-index-url https://pypi.org/simple/\n--trusted-host pypi.internal.example.com\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automating this with a tool like "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pip-audit",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "trivy",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in CI catches known-CVE packages before they reach production. A dependency scanner should run on every pull request and block merges if a critical CVE is found."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scan_dependencies.py \u2014 run in CI after pip-compile\nimport subprocess, sys, json\n\ndef audit_and_fail_on_critical():\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"pip-audit\", \"--format=json\", \"--requirement=requirements.txt\"],\n        capture_output=True, text=True,\n    )\n    report = json.loads(result.stdout)\n    critical = [\n        v for pkg in report.get(\"dependencies\", [])\n        for v in pkg.get(\"vulns\", [])\n        if v.get(\"fix_versions\") is not None  # has a known fix \u2192 block\n    ]\n    if critical:\n        for v in critical:\n            print(f\"BLOCK: {v['id']} in {v['package']} \u2014 {v['description'][:80]}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    print(\"No actionable vulnerabilities found.\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    audit_and_fail_on_critical()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM API Provider Risks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Calling an external LLM API means sending your prompts \u2014 which may contain sensitive context \u2014 to a third-party system. Risks include:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Training data leakage:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " some providers use API inputs for model training unless explicitly opted out."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompt logging:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " the provider's logging infrastructure may retain prompts for debugging."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Response tampering:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " a compromised provider (or MITM on the TLS session) could inject malicious text."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Availability dependency:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " provider outages cascade into agent failures."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, httpx, ssl, certifi\n\n# Enforce strict TLS and certificate pinning for the LLM API endpoint.\n# This prevents MITM attacks even if an intermediate CA is compromised.\n\nANTHROPIC_CERT_FINGERPRINT = (\n    # SHA-256 fingerprint of api.anthropic.com's leaf certificate.\n    # Re-pin after every cert rotation (track in your infra repo).\n    \"AB:CD:EF:01:23:45:67:89:AB:CD:EF:01:23:45:67:89:\"\n    \"AB:CD:EF:01:23:45:67:89:AB:CD:EF:01:23:45:67:89\"\n)\n\ndef build_pinned_client() -> anthropic.Anthropic:\n    ctx = ssl.create_default_context(cafile=certifi.where())\n    # Optionally set minimum TLS version\n    ctx.minimum_version = ssl.TLSVersion.TLSv1_3\n    transport = httpx.HTTPSTransport(ssl_context=ctx)\n    http_client = httpx.Client(transport=transport)\n    return anthropic.Anthropic(http_client=http_client)\n\n# Scrub sensitive fields from the prompt before sending\nSCRUB_KEYS = {\"ssn\", \"credit_card\", \"password\", \"api_key\", \"secret\"}\n\ndef scrub_before_send(messages: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:\n    import re, copy\n    cleaned = copy.deepcopy(messages)\n    pattern = re.compile(\n        r'\\b(ssn|credit.?card|password|api.?key|secret)\\b[^\\n]{0,40}',\n        re.IGNORECASE,\n    )\n    for msg in cleaned:\n        if isinstance(msg.get(\"content\"), str):\n            msg[\"content\"] = pattern.sub(\"[REDACTED]\", msg[\"content\"])\n    return cleaned\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector Database and RAG Backend Risks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retrieval-Augmented Generation pipelines often depend on a hosted vector database (Pinecone, Weaviate, Qdrant, etc.). If that service is compromised or misconfigured, an attacker can:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Poison the index:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " insert documents that carry prompt-injection payloads, altering every downstream agent response."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Exfiltrate embeddings:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " embedding vectors partially reconstruct the source text \u2014 a data-breach even without raw text access."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cross-tenant data exposure:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " multi-tenant SaaS vector DBs may leak documents across namespaces if access controls are misconfigured."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\nimport hashlib, hmac, json\n\nINGEST_SIGNING_KEY = b\"change-me-in-production\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass SignedChunk:\n    text: str\n    metadata: dict\n    signature: str  # HMAC-SHA256 over (text + sorted metadata)\n\ndef sign_chunk(text: str, metadata: dict) -> SignedChunk:\n    payload = json.dumps({\"text\": text, \"meta\": dict(sorted(metadata.items()))},\n                         sort_keys=True, ensure_ascii=True).encode()\n    sig = hmac.new(INGEST_SIGNING_KEY, payload, hashlib.sha256).hexdigest()\n    return SignedChunk(text=text, metadata=metadata, signature=sig)\n\ndef verify_chunk(chunk: SignedChunk) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Call this on every retrieved chunk before injecting into the prompt.\"\"\"\n    payload = json.dumps({\"text\": chunk.text,\n                          \"meta\": dict(sorted(chunk.metadata.items()))},\n                         sort_keys=True, ensure_ascii=True).encode()\n    expected = hmac.new(INGEST_SIGNING_KEY, payload, hashlib.sha256).hexdigest()\n    # constant-time comparison\n    return hmac.compare_digest(expected, chunk.signature)\n\ndef safe_retrieve(raw_chunks: list[dict]) -> list[str]:\n    results = []\n    for raw in raw_chunks:\n        chunk = SignedChunk(**raw)\n        if not verify_chunk(chunk):\n            # Log and skip; do NOT inject unsigned content into the prompt\n            raise ValueError(f\"Chunk signature mismatch: {chunk.metadata}\")\n        results.append(chunk.text)\n    return results\n"
          }
        ]
      },
