      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Third-party risk in agentic pipelines spans the full dependency graph: packages, LLM providers, vector stores, orchestration frameworks, REST APIs, and telemetry vendors. Each requires a distinct set of controls \u2014 hash pinning, scope restriction, payload signing, or sanitisation before egress. The common thread is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "never unconditionally trust",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " code, data, or credentials that cross a third-party boundary, and always apply the narrowest possible permission scope for each integration."
          }
        ]
